        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 4:25AM EDT by NWS Buffalo NY</headline>
        <description>Area webcams continue to show fog along the the Niagara River
from the vicinity of Grand Island northward into southwestern
Niagara county early this morning...including portions of the
Niagara Falls area. Some of this fog is locally dense in
spots...with visibilities down to a quarter mile or less.

If you will be travelling through this area early this morning...
be sure to slow down and be prepared for rapid changes in
visibility. The fog is expected to dissipate after sunrise.
</description>
